msgctxt "mn121:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 121"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 121"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn121:0.2"
msgid "Cūḷasuññatasutta"
msgstr "The Shorter Discourse on Emptiness"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.104"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn121:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn121:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, "
"the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn121:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Ānanda came out of retreat and went to "
"the Buddha. He bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn121:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Ekamidaṃ, bhante, samayaṃ bhagavā sakkesu viharati nagarakaṃ nāma sakyānaṃ "
"nigamo."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, this one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sakyans where "
"they have a town named Nagaraka."

msgctxt "mn121:3.2"
msgid "Tattha me, bhante, bhagavato sammukhā sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr "There I heard and learned this in the presence of the Buddha:"

msgctxt "mn121:3.3"
msgid "‘suññatāvihārenāhaṃ, ānanda, etarahi bahulaṃ viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘Ānanda, these days I usually practice the meditation on emptiness.’"

msgctxt "mn121:3.4"
msgid "Kacci metaṃ, bhante, sussutaṃ suggahitaṃ sumanasikataṃ sūpadhāritan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"I trust I properly heard, learned, attended, and remembered that from the "
"Buddha?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.105"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn121:3.5"
msgid ""
"“Taggha te etaṃ, ānanda, sussutaṃ suggahitaṃ sumanasikataṃ sūpadhāritaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Indeed, Ānanda, you properly heard, learned, attended, and remembered that."

#. VAR: etarahipi → etarahi ca (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: Pubbepāhaṃ → pubbecāhaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn121:3.6"
msgid "Pubbepāhaṃ, ānanda, etarahipi suññatāvihārena bahulaṃ viharāmi."
msgstr "Now, as before, I usually practice the meditation on emptiness."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
msgctxt "mn121:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, ānanda, ayaṃ migāramātupāsādo suñño hatthigavassavaḷavena, suñño "
"jātarūparajatena, suñño itthipurisasannipātena atthi cevidaṃ asuññataṃ "
"yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Consider this stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother. It’s empty of elephants, "
"cows, horses, and mares; of gold and money; and of gatherings of men and "
"women."

msgctxt "mn121:4.2"
msgid "bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paṭicca ekattaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"There is only this that is not emptiness, namely, the oneness dependent on "
"the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "mn121:4.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, ānanda, bhikkhu amanasikaritvā gāmasaññaṃ, amanasikaritvā "
"manussasaññaṃ, araññasaññaṃ paṭicca manasi karoti ekattaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant—ignoring the perception of the village and the "
"perception of people—focuses on the oneness dependent on the perception of "
"wilderness."

msgctxt "mn121:4.4"
msgid ""
"Tassa araññasaññāya cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati adhimuccati."
msgstr ""
"Their mind becomes eager, confident, settled, and decided in that perception "
"of wilderness."

msgctxt "mn121:4.5"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

msgctxt "mn121:4.6"
msgid ""
"‘ye assu darathā gāmasaññaṃ paṭicca tedha na santi, ye assu darathā "
"manussasaññaṃ paṭicca tedha na santi, atthi cevāyaṃ darathamattā yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘Here there is no stress due to the perception of village or the perception "
"of people."

msgctxt "mn121:4.7"
msgid "araññasaññaṃ paṭicca ekattan’ti."
msgstr ""
"There is only this modicum of stress, namely the oneness dependent on the "
"perception of wilderness.’"

msgctxt "mn121:4.8"
msgid ""
"So ‘suññamidaṃ saññāgataṃ gāmasaññāyā’ti pajānāti, ‘suññamidaṃ saññāgataṃ "
"manussasaññāyā’ti pajānāti, ‘atthi cevidaṃ asuññataṃ yadidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘This field of perception is empty of the perception of the "
"village. It is empty of the perception of people."

msgctxt "mn121:4.9"
msgid "araññasaññaṃ paṭicca ekattan’ti."
msgstr ""
"There is only this that is not emptiness, namely the oneness dependent on "
"the perception of wilderness.’"

msgctxt "mn121:4.10"
msgid ""
"Iti yañhi kho tattha na hoti tena taṃ suññaṃ samanupassati, yaṃ pana tattha "
"avasiṭṭhaṃ hoti taṃ ‘santamidaṃ atthī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"And so they regard it as empty of what is not there, but as to what remains "
"they understand that it is present."

msgctxt "mn121:4.11"
msgid ""
"Evampissa esā, ānanda, yathābhuccā avipallatthā parisuddhā suññatāvakkanti "
"bhavati."
msgstr "That’s how emptiness is born in them—genuine, undistorted, and pure."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
